Walked into this joint and with my Timbs and my fitted Yankees cap, bought a chop cheese sandwich. Stomped out some large rats with my Timbs, poured out an ounce for the homies. Pretty typical day for a woke New York boi.
its a cool spot to hang out with friends. depending who's the dj it can either be empty or packed.  They serve beers from the wid-west. Friendly vibes and drama free.

I had a great, free drinking time there for New year's Eve. There was a viewing of Purple Rain, but no audio. That was the bad part...  Otherwise cool bartenders and quaint environment on a desolate back street.

(Translated by Google) A bar that saved us from the torrential water. Their beer selection is a nice surprise.  (Original) Un bar qui nous a sauvé de trombes d'eau. Leurs sélection de bière est une bonne surprise.
No diet coke. No apple juice. Beer seems good. I didn't try food.

Great neighborhood spot, they always have a good beer selection (HMMM Simple Sour <3) and outdoor seating. Their weekend brunch is good and no fuss, but get there early, it runs out fast. When they do Karaoke, it's the bomb

Nice wine selection, dont know about the beers. Kitchen open late (which is really good for the area) only think wrong they dont sell sodas or have ice

My favorite bar in the universe of Jefferson L train stop drinking establishments. Good, ever-rotating, beer selection. It seems that they have a extensive wine menu though I have never explored it. The sandwich menu is nothing to write home about but it does the trick. Very much recommend.

Nice looking place, but service was not good at all. We had to wait a full hour for our burritos. And... they were so mediocre - I felt like I was eating scrambled eggs stuffed into a tortilla- very "gringo" version of a burrito. Being there seemed like the place was incredibly understaffed and not ready for the number of customers.
Good earthy wine

Before going to Bunna Cafe we thought we would check out a drinking establishment in Bushwick.  We were intrigued by The Bodega because it was listed as a Spanish-influenced wine bar.  When I hear "wine bar" I have a certain image in my head.  The Bodega isn't what I think of when I think wine bar.  It seems to be a regular bar that has wine.  There didn't seem to be a mind-blowing amount of wine available.  My biggest issue with The Bodega was the service.  My wife and our friend saw that there was a wine on special for $8.  They even referenced it when ordering.  I ordered a beer that was a dollar off, so $6.  I thought the bill was going to be $22.  It was $24.  I asked the bartender and he said the wines were $9 each.  I pointed to the special and he had no idea which wine that special was referring to.  Even though I expressed my concern about the price difference he made no effort to remedy the situation; instead, he simply handed me the credit card receipt.  If you have a special listed for $8 and then people order that special, you should give it to them for that price.  Acting oblivious and ignoring the customer's concerns is no way to run a business.  Or maybe it is because he got $2 more out of me. No need to return to The Bodega.
Great place for wine and small plates at dusk ❤️
Great brunch!
Win on tap. Why would you not go here?!
good brunch at the bar

The service is awful and the food doesn't make a great impression. If you choose to sit outside, the wait staff does not check up on you very often. They run out of brunch items quickly. Honestly, the experience was not anything special. I probably will not return.
Food was overpriced and bland. Got charged for a drink I didn't order and the bartender was very rude the entire time. So many better, cheaper, and friendlier places less than a block away.

Very great bar with a nice selection of wine and beer.  Surprisingly enough I was excited to find out this place serves brunch on the weekends.  Brunch is actually pretty good.  Service is quick and the food is delicious.  Never too busy so you rarely have to wait for a seat.

Excellent draft beer list with some hard to find selections on tap. Love the mural on the side if the building. It's a great accent for the neighborhood. Owners Ben and Gina also have Heavy Woods located a few blocks away on Willloughby and Wykoff.
Excellent food and well-curated wine and beer selections too. A great find.
This place is awesome! Small and completely nondescript from the outside, but they have a good draft selection and the small food menu is all executed excellently.
One of the best priced beer selection ever. And the sandwiches are superior.

Winos and beer fanatics love this Bushwick hangout a block. There's always a spot for you at the bar, and now that they serve food, it's a great spot for a sandwich and a boozy lunch. While not great for crowds, it's an intimate place to meet your close friends or a first date.
A perfectly unsnooty spot to drink wine and hang out. Come on Tuesday nights for their off-beat movie screenings.
